abstract: The company, formerly featured in the reality show “Breaking Pointe,” presented the premiere of a piece by Helen Pickett and three other works.
snippet: The company, formerly featured in the reality show “Breaking Pointe,” presented the premiere of a piece by Helen Pickett and three other works.
lead_paragraph: Ballet West has been in existence since 1963, but this Salt Lake City company didn’t gain national prominence until it became the focus of “Breaking Pointe,” a reality show more consumed by the dancers’ backstage lives than ballet. The program ran on the CW network for two seasons beginning in 2012. Now in the a five-night run at the Joyce Theater, Ballet West had a chance to put the emphasis back where it belongs, on dancing.

abstract: The hippie youth exploitation movies “The Wild Angels” and “Psych-Out” are offerings from American International Pictures at the studio’s most lurid and psychedelic.
snippet: The hippie youth exploitation movies “The Wild Angels” and “Psych-Out” are offerings from American International Pictures at the studio’s most lurid and psychedelic.
lead_paragraph: American International Pictures, the studio that pioneered the low-budget drive-in fare of the 1950s, specialized in two genres: horror films and youth pictures. Often, the two modes were conflated. In 1957, AIP unleashed “I Was a Teenage Werewolf”; in 1966, the studio brought forth “The Wild Angels.”

abstract: A new Showtime film about Smith, who led North Carolina’s basketball program and died last month, presents a uniformly positive view of a major figure in college sports history.
snippet: A new Showtime film about Smith, who led North Carolina’s basketball program and died last month, presents a uniformly positive view of a major figure in college sports history.
lead_paragraph: “Dean Smith,” the new documentary about the North Carolina basketball coach, is purely a homage. The portrait is not of a difficult or meanspirited man but of one whom any recruit’s parents would want to have in their home: polite, old-fashioned, supportive, averse to cursing (but not occasional sarcasm), hypercompetitive, humble, colorblind and pro-education (really).

abstract: Law enforcement groups also mourned the death of an officer in San Jose, Calif., who was fatally shot after responding to a call about a suicidal man.

lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — An afternoon of gunfire and fear in eastern Wisconsin ended Tuesday with a devastating toll: Two banks robbed, a bystander shot dead and a rookie state trooper, on his first day patrolling solo, slain in a firefight while confronting and killing the suspect.

abstract: When Chelsea Clinton’s husband, Marc Mezvinsky, co-founded an investment firm, Clinton family friends took an interest, illustrating how politics, family and finance can intersect.
snippet: When Chelsea Clinton’s husband, Marc Mezvinsky, co-founded an investment firm, Clinton family friends took an interest, illustrating how politics, family and finance can intersect.
lead_paragraph: Since marrying Chelsea Clinton five years ago, Marc Mezvinsky, a money manager, appears to have settled into his life as Bill and Hillary Clinton’s son-in-law. He has regularly appeared at charitable events, once introducing the former president at the Clinton Foundation’s celebrity poker tournament by dryly saying, “You may have heard of my father-in-law.” And at the recent N.B.A. All-Star Game, Mr. Mezvinsky took a seat next to Mr. Clinton and his partner in charitable endeavors, Dikembe Mutombo, the former basketball star.

abstract: The chilling progression of a Minnesota man suggests that the Islamic State may rely on recruiters inside the United States and shows how hard it is to predict who will be swept away by ideological fervor.

lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — Reading back over Abdi Nur’s Twitter feed, his chilling progression from the basketball courts of South Minneapolis to the battlefields of Syria is clear.

abstract: After a bruising campaign focused on his failings, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu seemed all but certain to form a new government, though he offended many in the process.
snippet: After a bruising campaign focused on his failings, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu seemed all but certain to form a new government, though he offended many in the process.
lead_paragraph: TEL AVIV — After a bruising campaign focused on his failings, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel won a clear victory in Tuesday’s elections and seemed all but certain to form a new government and serve a fourth term, though he offended many voters and alienated allies in the process.
